They've finally gone.

232
00:13:31,852 --> 00:13:34,313
It's better to let them go one time, yeah.

233
00:13:34,396 --> 00:13:35,689
Better to get it out of the way.

234
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:37,525
- It was always bound to happen.
- Yeah.

235
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:46,283
It can't be helped.

236
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:48,202
He said he wanted to go.

237
00:13:48,285 --> 00:13:49,912
I guess I'll just be a bit sad.

238
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:52,164
Very sad.

239
00:13:57,461 --> 00:13:59,880
The person I'd like to go
to Paradise with…

240
00:14:02,591 --> 00:14:04,176
is Lim Su-been.

241
00:14:05,427 --> 00:14:08,848
Oh, Hee-sun hasn't been there either,
come to think of it.

242
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:10,057
Oh, you're right.

243
00:14:10,140 --> 00:14:13,060
If Su-been's picked her this time,
she's going, right?

244
00:14:13,143 --> 00:14:14,270
Yeah, she will.

245
00:14:14,353 --> 00:14:17,106
- Totally possible.
- There's a chance.

246
00:14:17,189 --> 00:14:18,858
Yeah, he said, "Let's have fun together."

247
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:21,026
And he also said he was interested.

248
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:28,993
I felt like Su-been still, kind of,
had a thing with Mina Sue,

249
00:14:29,076 --> 00:14:31,495
even if they were both
trying to act like they didn't.

250
00:14:31,579 --> 00:14:32,413
LAST NIGHT

251
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:33,706
Oh, there's no one here.

252
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:37,167
Oh, we're just gonna chat in here.

253
00:14:37,251 --> 00:14:38,127
Sure.

254
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:40,546
Good luck.

255
00:14:42,256 --> 00:14:44,717
"Good luck"? What?

256
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:47,219
Oh, apparently, she was sick,
did you know?

257
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:53,225
I guess he's feeling this way

258
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:55,936
because he hasn't been
to Paradise with me yet.

259
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,272
- Oh, yeah.
- Confidence.

260
00:14:58,355 --> 00:15:01,609
Su-been, just go with her this once.
She's put in so much effort.

261
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:03,611
- He should get to know her.
- At the very least.

262
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:07,197
I mean, if I don't get to go
to Paradise today…

263
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,535
Ugh, I don't even know.

264
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:24,757
PARK HEE-SUN

265
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:28,886
CHOI MINA SUE

266
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:31,013
- No, not Mina Sue.
- He keeps looking at Mina Sue.

267
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,556
- Not that one.
- Oh!

268
00:15:35,392 --> 00:15:38,187
<i>The guy who has been matched</i>
<i>with Park Hee-sun…</i>

269
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:47,446
<i>…is Lim Su-been.</i>

270
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:50,616
Oh, thank goodness!

271
00:15:50,699 --> 00:15:53,410
There you go.
He did say he was curious about her.

272
00:15:53,494 --> 00:15:55,746
Nice, great result. Just what we wanted.

273
00:15:55,829 --> 00:15:56,789
Wow.

274
00:15:56,872 --> 00:15:59,375
- So Su-been didn't choose Mina Sue either?
- No.

275
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:01,502
Everything worked out today.
It's all good.

276
00:16:01,585 --> 00:16:05,464
But these people really are something.
They're so unpredictable.

277
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:07,758
- They're all young.
- Yeah, they're young.

278
00:16:07,841 --> 00:16:09,551
- Their energy<i>…</i>
- Wow.

279
00:16:10,386 --> 00:16:11,929
<i>…is Lim Su-been.</i>

280
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:15,391
<i>Lim Su-been, please make your way outside.</i>

281
00:16:22,189 --> 00:16:24,984
- Aw, she's thrilled.
- The biggest smile in ages.

282
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,343
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

283
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:53,303
You don't have much stuff.

284
00:16:53,387 --> 00:16:54,388
Just one bag.

285
00:16:54,888 --> 00:16:56,015
Is it heavy?

286
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:57,182
No.

287
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:02,229
Your first trip.

288
00:17:04,565 --> 00:17:07,609
- Time to eat some meat.
- Let's go. Let's do it.

289
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:10,946
The weather is perfect for Paradise.

290
00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:15,075
I was so nervous.

291
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:17,828
About what?

292
00:17:17,911 --> 00:17:19,288
That it wouldn't happen.

293
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:22,583
- Oh, you were worried?
- Mmm.

294
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,210
Seriously.

295
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:33,343
- I hope this makes him see her appeal.
- I hope it works out.

296
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:35,345
This Paradise trip kind of feels like…

297
00:17:35,929 --> 00:17:38,682
everyone's going with the person
they've been curious about.

298
00:17:38,766 --> 00:17:40,684
I'm looking forward to all of that.

299
00:17:48,484 --> 00:17:50,694
Oh, my gosh!

300
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,168
Do you like nature?

301
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:08,754
Yeah, I like spending time in nature.

302
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:13,258
Even when I travel, I always make sure
to spend time in nature.

303
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:14,301
Ah.

304
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:18,472
I haven't been to Bali yet.
I really want to go.

305
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:21,475
Bali? Bali? I've been there.

306
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:24,937
But, apparently, couples who go
to Bali together end up breaking up.

307
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:26,188
Really?

308
00:18:26,271 --> 00:18:27,731
It's a popular belief.

309
00:18:28,232 --> 00:18:29,858
- Then we shouldn't go.
- Huh?

310
00:18:29,942 --> 00:18:31,276
We shouldn't go.

311
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:36,907
That was pretty direct.

312
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:51,672
Oh, it's…

313
00:18:51,755 --> 00:18:52,923
Swapped.

314
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:58,137
- What?
- I was here with Su-been last time.

315
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:04,768
What did you do?

316
00:19:13,235 --> 00:19:15,529
Welcome to my territory.

317
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:17,906
- Good.
- Good.

318
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,660
You want to drive, right?

319
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:23,120
- Are you gonna drive?
- What?

320
00:19:23,203 --> 00:19:24,538
- I think I'll drive.
- Yeah, I--

321
00:19:24,621 --> 00:19:26,290
- I want to drive.
- I know.

322
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:28,375
Do you even like to drive?

323
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:30,586
Drive? Yeah, I told you.

324
00:19:31,086 --> 00:19:32,629
- Aren't you bad at it?
- Huh?

325
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:34,131
Aren't you bad at it?

326
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:37,301
- I'm the best driver.
- Oh.

327
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:43,307
Oh, my gosh. This is so cool!

328
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:44,683
What is this?

329
00:19:46,810 --> 00:19:48,729
Is this how it's supposed to look?

330
00:19:48,812 --> 00:19:51,565
Seriously, what is this?
Hee-sun looks unhappy.

331
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:54,484
Oh, my gosh. This is so cool!

332
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:55,652
- Wow.
- Oh, my gosh.

333
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:04,786
- Seung-il didn't look too happy.
- He's looking the other way.

334
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,456
He didn't pay much attention at first,
but they just kept going,

335
00:20:07,539 --> 00:20:09,166
and he was like, "Huh, what the hell?"

336
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:12,377
All right, what's for dinner?

337
00:20:12,461 --> 00:20:14,671
Tell me, what's on the menu?

338
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:18,091
- It's <i>dakdoritang.</i>
- I can't believe this!

339
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:20,886
- We're having spicy chicken.
- Yay!

340
00:20:20,969 --> 00:20:23,931
- I'm gonna have two bowls of rice!
- I'm excited for this.

341
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:26,391
There's kimchi, too.
Isn't there kimchi as well?

342
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:29,603
Should we also make some fried rice?

343
00:20:29,686 --> 00:20:31,480
- Yes. Good idea.
- Let's do it.

344
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:34,399
- We should.
- I'll have two bowls of this.

345
00:20:35,275 --> 00:20:36,652
Awesome.

346
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:39,404
Well, first of all,

347
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:42,950
- I'm feeling just yeah.
- Just yeah?

348
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:45,202
Yeah. Just not feeling great.

349
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:46,995
- I'm okay.
- Why? What's up?

350
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:48,789
I'm okay. Really, I'm fine.

351
00:20:49,373 --> 00:20:52,876
Her mood just went from
"I'm gonna have two bowls"

352
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,336
to deflated.

353
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:56,421
- That's forced excitement.
- You can tell

354
00:20:56,505 --> 00:20:58,298
she's forcing herself to act happy.

355
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:03,637
Yeah, well, I made my feelings clear,
but if he doesn't like me, what can I do?

356
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,973
- He never said he doesn't like you.
- No.

357
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:09,226
Maybe he wants a little escape.

358
00:21:09,309 --> 00:21:10,560
"A little escape"?

359
00:21:11,144 --> 00:21:14,064
- A little escape.
- He just wants to find out about her.

360
00:21:14,147 --> 00:21:16,984
I know, but he might like her
more than me.

361
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:20,153
You should just go to him and be like…

362
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:22,864
"How could you let go of someone
as great as I am?"

363
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:23,991
- Good idea.
- Mmm.

364
00:21:24,074 --> 00:21:26,576
Or like, "Who do you think you are,
letting me go?"

365
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:28,870
Oh, yeah, I like that one.

366
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:32,541
You're right. I am a great person,
so I'm not overly concerned about it.

367
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:34,543
- Good. I'm glad.
- Mmm.

368
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:37,254
I'm gonna have two bowls of rice.

369
00:21:39,214 --> 00:21:40,757
Mmm. I'm really hungry.

370
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,720
- Her eyes are so sad.
- You can see it in her eyes.

371
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:49,933
PARADISE
KIM GO-EUN & SHIN HYEON-WOO

372
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:53,478
- Wow. Amazing.
- This looks so good.

373
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:55,564
- Bon appétit.
- Bon appétit.

374
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:10,329
I can handle this much.

375
00:22:11,204 --> 00:22:13,498
- Do you mind?
- Okay.

376
00:22:15,959 --> 00:22:17,377
Here you go.

377
00:22:17,919 --> 00:22:19,212
Cheers.

378
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:31,141
How is it?

379
00:22:31,725 --> 00:22:32,726
- Is it good?
- Mmm.

380
00:22:38,607 --> 00:22:39,566
How old are you?

381
00:22:41,526 --> 00:22:44,613
- I'm 28.
- Mmm.

382
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:47,824
You're older than me.

383
00:22:48,992 --> 00:22:50,035
I'm 26.

384
00:22:51,995 --> 00:22:54,164
I'm glad you're older.

385
00:22:54,915 --> 00:22:56,124
Oh, you're glad?

386
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:59,920
- Wow. So you're 26?
- Yeah.

387
00:23:00,003 --> 00:23:03,215
- I was really worried.
- I was a bit worried, too.

388
00:23:03,298 --> 00:23:05,759
I'll be more confident now.

389
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:10,347
So I'm guessing that
you might be a physical therapist

390
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:11,890
or something similar to that.

391
00:23:14,226 --> 00:23:16,895
- Physical therapist?
- Or something to do with sports.

392
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:19,064
Yeah, well…

393
00:23:20,982 --> 00:23:26,988
So, from elementary school,
through my sophomore year in college,

394
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:29,157
- I was an athlete.
- Mmm.

395
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:34,329
- And now, I am a coach of a sports team.
- Wow.

396
00:23:34,413 --> 00:23:36,206
Which sport? Judo or something?

397
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:38,375
- Handball.
- Wow!

398
00:23:38,458 --> 00:23:41,044
- Handball.
- Oh, handball.

399
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:41,962
Oh, really?

400
00:23:44,381 --> 00:23:46,716
<i>I work as a handball coach.</i>

401
00:23:50,053 --> 00:23:52,222
<i>I train an elite team,</i>
<i>working with students</i>

402
00:23:52,305 --> 00:23:54,975
<i>on the physical conditioning</i>
<i>needed for competitions.</i>

403
00:23:55,517 --> 00:23:58,186
<i>I work with them on things</i>
<i>like correcting their handball form</i>

404
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:01,898
<i>and teaching tactical strategies</i>
<i>for enhanced performance.</i>

405
00:24:04,443 --> 00:24:07,779
SHIN HYEON-WOO
BORN IN 1998, HANDBALL COACH

406
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:10,824
Wow. So interesting.

407
00:24:10,907 --> 00:24:14,369
Both of my shoulders
have been surgically repaired.

408
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:17,289
- That's why you went into coaching.
- Mmm-hmm.

409
00:24:17,372 --> 00:24:18,331
Right.

410
00:24:18,415 --> 00:24:19,749
That's why they're uneven.

411
00:24:20,292 --> 00:24:21,293
Wait, what?

412
00:24:21,376 --> 00:24:23,545
- This side is bigger.
- Oh!

413
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:25,172
Yeah, I see it.

414
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:27,674
How can it be this big? That's crazy.

415
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:30,469
They couldn't even them out at all.

416
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:38,518
- This burn is from a curling iron.
- Curling iron?

417
00:24:38,602 --> 00:24:39,603
Curling iron?

418
00:24:43,773 --> 00:24:46,818
I really need to work out.
They look pathetic.

419
00:24:46,902 --> 00:24:50,363
- Do you like exercise?
- But when I exercise, I can't lose weight.

420
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:54,534
- I'll teach you.
- Mmm.

421
00:24:54,618 --> 00:24:56,077
- How to exercise.
- Okay.

422
00:24:56,161 --> 00:24:57,579
You can come over every weekend.

423
00:24:57,662 --> 00:24:59,080
- Oh, sounds good.
- Yeah.

424
00:24:59,623 --> 00:25:01,875
You know, on weekends,
there's a surcharge, right?

425
00:25:01,958 --> 00:25:03,168
Oh, really?

426
00:25:03,251 --> 00:25:06,129
- Oops.
- I'm just kidding.

427
00:25:06,713 --> 00:25:09,257
I'm sorry. I'll pull myself together now.

428
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:11,801
Anything you want to know?

429
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:16,264
- What did you like about me initially?
- Ah.

430
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:21,895
- It was just, well, attraction.
- Mmm.

431
00:25:26,441 --> 00:25:27,817
When I looked in your eyes…

432
00:25:28,527 --> 00:25:29,569
It was your eyes.

433
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:32,531
- And every time you smiled,
- Mmm.

434
00:25:33,907 --> 00:25:36,409
I got butterflies.

435
00:25:39,037 --> 00:25:40,205
Mmm.

436
00:25:40,997 --> 00:25:43,291
- I just wasn't myself.
- Really?

437
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:47,879
That bad, huh?

438
00:25:48,463 --> 00:25:51,091
I don't know.
I felt like I was being really awkward.

439
00:25:51,174 --> 00:25:52,801
- Yeah, a little, honestly.
- Mmm.

440
00:25:53,343 --> 00:25:55,887
Are you usually like that
in front of a crush?

441
00:26:03,645 --> 00:26:04,688
Oh, okay.

442
00:26:05,897 --> 00:26:07,357
Then that one time…

443
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:13,154
when I got a cut here, I didn't even know.

444
00:26:14,614 --> 00:26:17,534
- But you kept asking me about it.
- Mmm.

445
00:26:23,039 --> 00:26:25,834
- And you were the only one who did that.
- Mmm.

446
00:26:25,917 --> 00:26:28,420
- Maybe only I saw it.
- Maybe.

447
00:26:28,962 --> 00:26:30,422
Why were you paying attention to me?

448
00:26:31,047 --> 00:26:33,717
- Oh, my gosh.
- I wish I'd realized it sooner.

449
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:43,101
- I've gone red now.
- In the face?

450
00:26:43,184 --> 00:26:45,645
Mmm. It's all red.

451
00:26:45,729 --> 00:26:47,689
- My face has gone red.
- Maybe it's the alcohol.

452
00:26:47,772 --> 00:26:49,983
- I wonder why.
- No, no, I meant me.

453
00:26:50,066 --> 00:26:52,694
- Oh, you? Why?
- I think my cheeks are getting a bit red.

454
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,988
Do you go red when you're drunk?

455
00:26:57,073 --> 00:26:58,950
I don't think so. Not usually, at least.

456
00:26:59,034 --> 00:27:01,411
- Then I guess you were embarrassed.
- I guess so.

457
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:11,087
- Want to go swim?
- Mmm.

458
00:27:16,217 --> 00:27:17,385
Oh, it's cold.

459
00:27:21,765 --> 00:27:22,724
The water…

460
00:27:29,105 --> 00:27:30,774
It's warm, right?

461
00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:32,192
Nice. Very nice.

462
00:27:33,693 --> 00:27:36,112
I've always wanted to do this.

463
00:27:36,696 --> 00:27:38,448
It's so cool.

464
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:40,617
You're so funny.

465
00:27:42,202 --> 00:27:44,204
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

466
00:27:46,748 --> 00:27:47,916
Mmm.

467
00:27:50,627 --> 00:27:51,753
Do you like the water?

468
00:27:51,836 --> 00:27:52,879
- Yeah.
- Mmm.

469
00:28:02,681 --> 00:28:04,849
- You wanna hold hands?
- Yeah. Let's do it.

470
00:28:09,771 --> 00:28:12,482
- I'm speeding up now.
- Oh, watch out behind you.

471
00:28:15,985 --> 00:28:16,986
You're cute.

472
00:28:17,070 --> 00:28:19,572
I can't swim.

473
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:23,118
I wish I could save this moment.

474
00:28:23,952 --> 00:28:26,579
Well, it'll be saved on Netflix forever.

475
00:28:26,663 --> 00:28:29,874
- That's right.
- That's right.

476
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:36,297
This is nice.

477
00:28:41,302 --> 00:28:42,762
- What is it, an eyelash?
- The mole.

478
00:28:43,304 --> 00:28:45,014
- Yeah.
- Is it drawn on?

479
