966
00:55:06,970 --> 00:55:08,013
You first.

967
00:55:09,806 --> 00:55:10,974
This looks really good.

968
00:55:11,057 --> 00:55:12,225
- Like this?
- Yeah.

969
00:55:16,229 --> 00:55:19,858
One, two, three.

970
00:55:20,525 --> 00:55:22,861
- I'll take one of you.
- Okay.

971
00:55:22,944 --> 00:55:26,114
One, two, three.

972
00:55:27,282 --> 00:55:28,616
I think it'll be good.

973
00:55:29,868 --> 00:55:31,578
Let's take one together.

974
00:55:38,126 --> 00:55:41,254
I did well, right?

975
00:55:41,338 --> 00:55:43,715
- They're so vibey. Yeah.
- Do you like it? Right?

976
00:55:43,798 --> 00:55:46,134
- This one's really nice.
- Right?

977
00:55:46,217 --> 00:55:47,802
- We look good together.
- Yeah.

978
00:55:49,304 --> 00:55:50,847
Finally, the meat is here.

979
00:55:50,930 --> 00:55:52,265
- Meat.
- Yeah.

980
00:55:53,183 --> 00:55:55,435
You get a big piece.

981
00:55:56,686 --> 00:55:57,687
Oh.

982
00:55:59,981 --> 00:56:00,982
Thank you.

983
00:56:02,025 --> 00:56:03,068
Ready?

984
00:56:03,151 --> 00:56:04,235
Cheers.

985
00:56:08,239 --> 00:56:10,492
Mmm…

986
00:56:12,410 --> 00:56:13,578
This is so good.

987
00:56:16,706 --> 00:56:18,917
- I'm happy.
- Yeah, same.

988
00:56:19,459 --> 00:56:21,920
I didn't get to eat much
in Paradise last time.

989
00:56:23,129 --> 00:56:26,758
Everyone seems to say they weren't able
to eat much on their first Paradise trip.

990
00:56:26,841 --> 00:56:29,969
Yeah. You seem to be enjoying the meal.

991
00:56:31,388 --> 00:56:34,682
- You feel comfortable with me?
- Yeah, we talked a lot before coming here.

992
00:56:34,766 --> 00:56:36,810
- We got to talk a lot.
- Exactly.

993
00:56:36,893 --> 00:56:39,187
The others went
without talking much beforehand.

994
00:56:41,398 --> 00:56:43,817
Let's cheers. Then tell me about your job.

995
00:56:43,900 --> 00:56:45,318
Oh, okay.

996
00:56:49,364 --> 00:56:50,657
I work in…

997
00:56:51,658 --> 00:56:54,744
global cosmetics for a company

998
00:56:54,828 --> 00:56:57,747
in their customer relationship
management department.

999
00:56:57,831 --> 00:56:58,790
Wow, okay.

1000
00:56:58,873 --> 00:57:02,794
I, like, analyze data on customers
and use that to form marketing strategies.

1001
00:57:03,336 --> 00:57:05,380
Oh…

1002
00:57:08,007 --> 00:57:09,801
<i>I'm majoring in information systems</i>

1003
00:57:09,884 --> 00:57:12,637
<i>at Carnegie Mellon University</i>
<i>in the United States.</i>

1004
00:57:15,849 --> 00:57:18,017
<i>The program at Carnegie Mellon University</i>

1005
00:57:18,101 --> 00:57:20,979
<i>is one of the most prestigious</i>
<i>and well respected in the US</i>

1006
00:57:21,062 --> 00:57:22,647
<i>when it comes to engineering.</i>

1007
00:57:22,730 --> 00:57:24,649
Carnegie Mellon? Wow.

1008
00:57:24,732 --> 00:57:27,485
Carnegie Mellon is literally
the best engineering school.

1009
00:57:27,569 --> 00:57:29,154
She's a brainy beauty.

1010
00:57:30,029 --> 00:57:32,657
<i>I'm currently gaining</i>
<i>some experience by interning</i>

1011
00:57:32,740 --> 00:57:34,367
<i>at a global cosmetics company.</i>

1012
00:57:35,660 --> 00:57:40,331
PARK HEE-SUN
CARNEGIE MELLON, INFORMATION SYSTEMS MAJOR

1013
00:57:40,415 --> 00:57:42,917
So she's smart and she's pretty.

1014
00:57:43,001 --> 00:57:45,462
- Isn't that unfair?
- That's totally cheating.

1015
00:57:46,004 --> 00:57:47,172
Oh, I knew it.

1016
00:57:47,255 --> 00:57:49,549
I had a feeling it was related to English
in some way.

1017
00:57:49,632 --> 00:57:51,426
I used to live in Canada when I was young.

1018
00:57:51,509 --> 00:57:53,595
Oh. And why did you leave there?

1019
00:57:54,345 --> 00:57:57,182
I went to study abroad
because I wanted to learn English.

1020
00:57:57,932 --> 00:58:00,685
I was on the cheerleading team as well,
tossing people and stuff.

1021
00:58:00,768 --> 00:58:02,353
You look like you'd be a good dancer.

1022
00:58:02,437 --> 00:58:04,689
- I could tumble, too.
- Huh?

1023
00:58:04,772 --> 00:58:06,399
Tumbling, cartwheels.

1024
00:58:07,066 --> 00:58:09,110
- You're lying.
- No, I'm being serious.

1025
00:58:09,194 --> 00:58:10,820
- Really?
- I can do cartwheels.

1026
00:58:11,946 --> 00:58:14,324
- That's kind of unexpected, honestly.
- Why?

1027
00:58:15,366 --> 00:58:18,411
- You look like the wind could blow you.
- Come on.

1028
00:58:18,495 --> 00:58:19,496
I had no idea.

1029
00:58:22,457 --> 00:58:23,458
So your age.

1030
00:58:23,541 --> 00:58:24,918
- My age?
- Mmm-hmm.

1031
00:58:27,754 --> 00:58:29,672
I was born in 2002.

1032
00:58:30,465 --> 00:58:31,758
- Really?
- Yeah.

1033
00:58:32,800 --> 00:58:33,801
What?

1034
00:58:34,385 --> 00:58:36,054
You're younger than I thought.

1035
00:58:36,137 --> 00:58:37,639
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1036
00:58:38,348 --> 00:58:41,851
So how old are you, then?
Am I old enough to talk to you informally?

1037
00:58:42,393 --> 00:58:43,811
You need to call me "<i>noona."</i>

1038
00:58:43,895 --> 00:58:45,855
- Call me "<i>noona." </i>Yeah.
- Really?

1039
00:58:45,939 --> 00:58:47,732
- How old are you?
- Call me "<i>noona."</i>

1040
00:58:51,110 --> 00:58:52,195
How old are you?

1041
00:58:53,321 --> 00:58:55,323
- Huh? Take a guess.
- When were you born?

1042
00:58:56,699 --> 00:58:59,035
- '02, '03.
- '02, '03?

1043
00:58:59,118 --> 00:59:00,537
Mmm…

1044
00:59:03,915 --> 00:59:05,458
- What?
- You're right.

1045
00:59:05,542 --> 00:59:06,918
- I am?
- Yeah, you are.

1046
00:59:07,001 --> 00:59:08,878
- So how old then?
- I was born in '03.

1047
00:59:09,546 --> 00:59:10,838
- '03?
- Yeah.

1048
00:59:10,922 --> 00:59:13,758
So I was right. How dare you?

1049
00:59:13,841 --> 00:59:15,718
You made me think I was the youngest.

1050
00:59:16,594 --> 00:59:17,804
Man!

1051
00:59:17,887 --> 00:59:19,556
- Okay.
- Oh, this is really…

1052
00:59:19,639 --> 00:59:22,350
I wanted to be older than you. Oh, well.

1053
00:59:22,433 --> 00:59:24,352
Hey, if you were the <i>noona…</i>

1054
00:59:24,435 --> 00:59:26,354
Thought we'd have a bigger age gap.

1055
00:59:27,272 --> 00:59:30,400
- We're basically the same age.
- We're equal, then?

1056
00:59:30,483 --> 00:59:32,777
No, we're not.

1057
00:59:32,860 --> 00:59:34,320
You don't decide that.

1058
00:59:35,446 --> 00:59:38,324
Did you call me "you"?
That was just a bit…

1059
00:59:38,825 --> 00:59:40,285
Mmm… "You."

1060
00:59:41,286 --> 00:59:42,328
Sorry.

1061
00:59:45,331 --> 00:59:46,332
That's crazy.

1062
00:59:50,545 --> 00:59:52,714
All right, baby, eat up.

1063
00:59:52,797 --> 00:59:54,465
Why "baby"?

1064
00:59:56,551 --> 00:59:58,136
- Wow.
- You told me that's your nickname.

1065
00:59:58,219 --> 00:59:59,345
Yeah, that's true.

1066
01:00:02,140 --> 01:00:03,349
Ever dated younger?

1067
01:00:03,433 --> 01:00:04,767
- Younger than me?
- Mmm-hmm.

1068
01:00:04,851 --> 01:00:06,185
No, I never have.

1069
01:00:06,269 --> 01:00:07,520
- Really?
- Yeah.

1070
01:00:10,189 --> 01:00:11,232
So I'm the first.

1071
01:00:12,525 --> 01:00:17,280
- You're not my girlfriend yet.
- No, that's not what I meant.

1072
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:19,407
We don't know yet if you'll be the first.

1073
01:00:20,158 --> 01:00:24,537
- I was kidding. Can't you just play along?
- You really went from zero to 100 there.

1074
01:00:25,580 --> 01:00:27,332
My mistake.

1075
01:00:27,832 --> 01:00:29,083
I'm scared to talk now.

1076
01:00:29,167 --> 01:00:31,836
I was kidding.
Wait, I just used two forks.

1077
01:00:36,257 --> 01:00:39,761
Is me saying "you" a bit weird?
How should I address you?

1078
01:00:41,137 --> 01:00:43,306
- Well, that's a tough one.
- Baby?

1079
01:00:43,389 --> 01:00:44,932
Is "baby" better?

1080
01:00:46,059 --> 01:00:48,102
How about "rice cake"?

1081
01:00:48,186 --> 01:00:50,355
- My friends do call me that, actually.
- Rice cake?

1082
01:00:50,438 --> 01:00:52,940
Like, baby or…
It sounds weird saying it myself.

1083
01:00:53,024 --> 01:00:55,610
- Your head's shaped like a baby's.
- My head?

1084
01:00:55,693 --> 01:00:58,571
- Yeah, I mean, your head's kind of--
- My head is round at the back.

1085
01:00:58,655 --> 01:01:00,740
- It pops out.
- But your forehead kind of--

1086
01:01:00,823 --> 01:01:02,283
True. It is like that.

1087
01:01:02,367 --> 01:01:05,703
You really have the head shape of a baby.

1088
01:01:05,787 --> 01:01:07,288
People say it's pretty.

1089
01:01:07,372 --> 01:01:08,998
A forehead like this is pretty.

1090
01:01:09,082 --> 01:01:11,668
Yeah, it's adorable, seriously.

1091
01:01:29,644 --> 01:01:31,521
I thought this was a staring contest.

1092
01:01:36,275 --> 01:01:38,945
These two are sharing some sweet moments.

1093
01:01:39,737 --> 01:01:41,197
It's awkward to watch.

1094
01:01:43,324 --> 01:01:44,575
Are you feeling okay?

1095
01:01:44,659 --> 01:01:45,785
Mmm.

1096
01:01:46,619 --> 01:01:47,954
- I'm good.
- Mmm.

1097
01:01:49,414 --> 01:01:50,415
I'm glad.

1098
01:01:51,833 --> 01:01:53,418
My face feels so warm.

1099
01:01:54,293 --> 01:01:57,004
- Oh, it's a bit red.
- It is, right?

1100
01:01:58,214 --> 01:02:00,049
- Oh, it's really hot.
- Is it too hot?

1101
01:02:00,133 --> 01:02:02,593
- Yeah.
- Why is it so hot?

1102
01:02:03,678 --> 01:02:06,597
I don't know. Is it because
you've had champagne or wine?

1103
01:02:07,724 --> 01:02:08,891
Are you okay?

1104
01:02:09,767 --> 01:02:12,603
- I'm okay.
- You're fine. So it's just me.

1105
01:02:12,687 --> 01:02:15,982
- You seem to be doing all right.
- Yeah, I'm totally fine.

1106
01:02:16,065 --> 01:02:18,151
- You just had--
- I'm having a great time.

1107
01:02:18,234 --> 01:02:20,737
I think I might be starting
to feel it a bit. Yeah.

1108
01:02:20,820 --> 01:02:21,904
I'm having fun.

1109
01:02:31,581 --> 01:02:33,040
So how was that for you?

1110
01:02:33,875 --> 01:02:35,543
Oh, for me?

1111
01:02:38,671 --> 01:02:41,466
- Today was the best day.
- Really?

1112
01:02:43,718 --> 01:02:44,802
Yeah, I think it was.

1113
01:02:46,804 --> 01:02:47,805
That's good.

1114
01:02:49,098 --> 01:02:53,728
I have this thing where when I'm talking
to someone, I feel one of two ways.

1115
01:02:55,354 --> 01:02:58,816
Either I click with this person,
or I click with this person,

1116
01:02:58,900 --> 01:03:00,943
but I also feel like
my energy is being drained.

1117
01:03:01,027 --> 01:03:02,361
- Mmm…
- That kind of thing.

1118
01:03:02,445 --> 01:03:04,197
Oh, I totally know what you mean.

1119
01:03:04,280 --> 01:03:05,865
There are two different things.

1120
01:03:08,201 --> 01:03:10,369
We've been in Inferno for a while now,

1121
01:03:10,870 --> 01:03:14,165
and you're the one I feel
the most comfortable talking to.

1122
01:03:14,248 --> 01:03:16,292
Mmm. I understand, yeah.

1123
01:03:16,375 --> 01:03:19,003
It's not that I feel comfortable
because I'm used to you.

1124
01:03:19,086 --> 01:03:20,838
I just feel at ease
when I'm talking to you,

1125
01:03:20,922 --> 01:03:22,507
- like, in my heart.
- Mmm.

1126
01:03:22,590 --> 01:03:24,717
- Or…
- We understand each other.

1127
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:25,802
Mmm.

1128
01:03:30,056 --> 01:03:32,391
I wanted to have more
in-depth chats with you.

1129
01:03:32,475 --> 01:03:33,476
Mmm.

1130
01:03:42,777 --> 01:03:44,654
- What?
- Nothing.

1131
01:03:45,488 --> 01:03:46,864
Am I not allowed to look at you?

1132
01:03:46,948 --> 01:03:48,866
I feel like you keep
smiling at me like this.

1133
01:03:51,202 --> 01:03:53,621
Spot on. Nice impression of me.

1134
01:04:04,799 --> 01:04:06,968
I don't want to go back.

1135
01:04:08,553 --> 01:04:10,096
Want to ditch it?

1136
01:04:10,179 --> 01:04:12,265
- Run away?
- Should we?

1137
01:04:12,849 --> 01:04:14,392
Yeah. Get the car.

1138
01:04:16,853 --> 01:04:18,312
- Let's go to Busan.
- To Busan?

1139
01:04:18,396 --> 01:04:20,398
- Yeah.
- Busan sounds good.

1140
01:04:22,817 --> 01:04:25,820
- They going on the run?
- They're cute.

1141
01:04:25,903 --> 01:04:28,072
Vibe's turned really nice
after a couple of drinks.

1142
01:04:28,155 --> 01:04:30,658
Da-hee's doing this
for the first time this season.

1143
01:04:30,741 --> 01:04:32,618
Is this couple
making you feel a certain way?

1144
01:04:32,702 --> 01:04:34,662
Aren't these two just great together?

1145
01:04:34,745 --> 01:04:37,415
- Mmm.
- They are. When their eyes met just now,

1146
01:04:37,498 --> 01:04:39,834
- Yeah.
- I totally got butterflies.

1147
01:04:39,917 --> 01:04:43,671
When Su-been said he felt like
they were having a staring contest,

1148
01:04:43,754 --> 01:04:45,923
I think that was Hee-sun's
way of flirting.

1149
01:04:46,007 --> 01:04:47,967
She was definitely trying
to be playful with him.

1150
01:04:48,050 --> 01:04:48,968
She's so into him.

1151
01:04:49,051 --> 01:04:50,845
- That's right.
- Yeah.

1152
01:04:50,928 --> 01:04:54,056
And just now, they looked
at each other and locked eyes.

1153
01:04:54,140 --> 01:04:56,517
I get the feeling that
after this Paradise trip,

1154
01:04:56,601 --> 01:04:58,853
Su-been's heart
is going to be set on Hee-sun.

1155
01:04:58,936 --> 01:05:01,689
- This might seal the deal for him.
- I see.

1156
01:05:01,772 --> 01:05:04,942
And also, he said something about
how some people make you

1157
01:05:05,026 --> 01:05:08,946
feel super comfortable,
while others suck the energy out of you.

1158
01:05:09,030 --> 01:05:12,325
- You think he was referring to Mina Sue?
- I think so. That's my guess.

1159
01:05:12,408 --> 01:05:13,784
I think he probably was.

1160
01:05:13,868 --> 01:05:16,579
Whenever he talked to Mina Sue,
he felt she was draining his energy.

1161
01:05:16,662 --> 01:05:17,705
I can see that.

1162
01:05:17,788 --> 01:05:20,291
Talking to Mina Sue
leaves him emotionally drained.

1163
01:05:20,374 --> 01:05:23,586
But there are those who actually enjoy
this kind of emotional draining.

1164
01:05:23,669 --> 01:05:25,671
Some people need
that emotional roller coaster

1165
01:05:25,755 --> 01:05:28,299
to feel like their relationship
is exciting or real,

1166
01:05:28,382 --> 01:05:32,136
or they feel like something's missing,
while others find it totally exhausting.

1167
01:05:32,219 --> 01:05:34,263
- For sure.
- Because it's just the two of them,

1168
01:05:34,347 --> 01:05:36,098
they're able to fully focus on each other,

1169
01:05:36,182 --> 01:05:38,935
which I think leads
to greater attraction on both sides.

1170
01:05:40,519 --> 01:05:42,396
Have you bowled before?

1171
01:05:43,981 --> 01:05:46,525
- I don't do it often.
- I'm not great at it.

1172
01:05:47,526 --> 01:05:49,028
Don't laugh at me.

1173
01:05:49,612 --> 01:05:50,613
Mmm.

1174
01:05:51,238 --> 01:05:52,990
- Is this how you hold it?
- Mmm.

1175
01:05:53,074 --> 01:05:55,451
You see that line over there?
Go up to that line.

1176
01:05:55,534 --> 01:05:57,620
- I know that much.
- Oh, yeah?

1177
01:05:57,703 --> 01:06:00,289
- You think I'd throw it from here?
- I didn't mean to insult you.

1178
01:06:00,373 --> 01:06:02,583
Should I throw it from here?

1179
01:06:04,877 --> 01:06:06,170
Oh. Oh!

1180
01:06:06,921 --> 01:06:09,423
- Wow! How did that happen?
- Respect, respect.

1181
01:06:09,507 --> 01:06:10,758
- Dang. Whoa!
- Oh, nice.

1182
01:06:11,342 --> 01:06:12,343
I'm in trouble.

1183
01:06:14,053 --> 01:06:15,721
Whoa!

1184
01:06:15,805 --> 01:06:17,723
Oh, look who's here.

1185
01:06:20,810 --> 01:06:23,104
Oh, don't tell me it's Choi Mina Sue.

1186
01:06:25,481 --> 01:06:26,649
Is someone…

1187
01:06:27,441 --> 01:06:30,403
Oh, my… Oh! Whoa!

1188
01:06:32,446 --> 01:06:34,323
Oh, come on!

1189
01:06:34,407 --> 01:06:37,118
- What's wrong with them? Oh, seriously.
- Brought them deliberately.

1190
01:06:38,160 --> 01:06:40,830
<i>Single's Inferno, </i>baby!

1191
01:06:40,913 --> 01:06:43,541
Watch out.
Mina Sue's just got to power up.

1192
01:06:43,624 --> 01:06:46,419
Oh, my… Oh! Whoa!

1193
01:06:49,213 --> 01:06:50,840
There's some familiar faces.

1194
01:06:53,509 --> 01:06:55,553
- Fancy seeing you here.
- Hello.

1195
01:06:55,636 --> 01:06:57,430
- How was dinner?
- How are you?

1196
01:06:57,513 --> 01:06:59,265
- Great.
- It was so tasty.

1197
01:06:59,348 --> 01:07:00,766
- It was tasty.
- Unbelievable.

1198
01:07:00,850 --> 01:07:02,226
- Same here.
- Bowling.

1199
01:07:02,309 --> 01:07:04,395
This bowling alley is fancy.

1200
01:07:04,478 --> 01:07:06,063
- I feel out of place.
- Right?

1201
01:07:06,147 --> 01:07:09,191
- I like bowling.
- Are we gonna make a bet or what?

1202
01:07:10,776 --> 01:07:13,654
Whoever loses
has to grant the winner a wish.

1203
01:07:13,738 --> 01:07:15,698
- Just one each, okay?
- Sure. Whatever you want.

1204
01:07:15,781 --> 01:07:16,866
All right.

1205
01:07:17,575 --> 01:07:19,285
Look, she's nervous.

1206
01:07:19,368 --> 01:07:20,995
- Her face has changed.
- Yeah.

1207
01:07:21,078 --> 01:07:22,997
Just leave them alone for one day.

1208
01:07:23,080 --> 01:07:25,332
Just when Hee-sun
was finally in her element.

1209
01:07:25,416 --> 01:07:26,876
I know.

1210
01:07:30,046 --> 01:07:31,964
- Let's toast?
- Let's toast.

1211
01:07:32,590 --> 01:07:33,799
Cheers!

1212
01:07:33,883 --> 01:07:37,094
- Oh, what'd you have for dinner?
- We had some steak.

1213
01:07:37,178 --> 01:07:38,971
- Sounds fancy.
- So good.

1214
01:07:39,889 --> 01:07:40,973
How about you?

1215
01:07:41,057 --> 01:07:42,767
- We had that, too.
- Mmm.

1216
01:07:42,850 --> 01:07:44,977
- I forget the…
- Did you go to a restaurant?

1217
01:07:45,061 --> 01:07:47,188
What was it called?
It was three syllables.

1218
01:07:47,271 --> 01:07:49,857
- I can't remember.
- Did you eat a lot?

1219
01:07:49,940 --> 01:07:51,984
- Yeah, just enough.
- I remember the location, but…

1220
01:07:56,906 --> 01:07:59,492
So do you want to go first or third, Mina?

1221
01:07:59,575 --> 01:08:01,619
I think I'll go first because it's a bit…

1222
01:08:02,203 --> 01:08:03,204
All right.

1223
01:08:03,913 --> 01:08:06,040
- Let's go!
- Watch out. It's Hee-sun.

1224
01:08:06,582 --> 01:08:09,043
- Rice cake.
- Sorry, rice cake.

1225
01:08:10,503 --> 01:08:12,254
- Let's go.
- Go.

1226
01:08:15,841 --> 01:08:17,093
Okay.

1227
01:08:19,762 --> 01:08:22,556
- Very nice. Good job.
- Awesome. Wow.

1228
01:08:22,640 --> 01:08:24,225
It's all right.

1229
01:08:24,308 --> 01:08:26,644
You aim too high,
trying to get a strike on your first try.

1230
01:08:26,727 --> 01:08:29,063
- Practically flew away.
- Like whoosh!

1231
01:08:30,648 --> 01:08:33,609
- Oh, looks good.
- Come on, come on, come on!

1232
01:08:33,692 --> 01:08:36,654
- Wow.
- How many points is that, one?

1233
01:08:36,737 --> 01:08:38,697
Great. I'm feeling less pressure now.

1234
01:08:38,781 --> 01:08:40,866
No, seriously.

1235
01:08:40,950 --> 01:08:43,035
Rice cake. Let's go, rice cake.

1236
01:08:44,286 --> 01:08:46,580
- Oh!
- Oh, no!

1237
01:08:46,664 --> 01:08:48,749
- That was awful.
- You're better than me.

1238
01:08:48,833 --> 01:08:51,669
- Not bad, not bad.
- No, not bad.

1239
01:08:51,752 --> 01:08:53,129
That was four pins.

1240
01:08:53,838 --> 01:08:55,422
Just aim for the middle. Yeah.

1241
01:09:00,636 --> 01:09:02,096
I keep reaching for the beer.

1242
01:09:03,180 --> 01:09:04,849
Oh, no! I think it's a miss!

1243
01:09:05,808 --> 01:09:07,935
- Oh, that was close.
- I slipped.

1244
01:09:08,018 --> 01:09:09,937
Hee-sun, you're pretty good.

1245
01:09:10,020 --> 01:09:12,690
- I think you're better than me.
- It's okay. It's better than one.

1246
01:09:12,773 --> 01:09:15,442
- Whoa, Hee-sun. Did you see that?
- See what?

1247
01:09:16,026 --> 01:09:18,863
- She stood right up against him.
- She's marking her territory.

1248
01:09:18,946 --> 01:09:21,699
She's claiming what's hers, isn't she?
Like this.

1249
01:09:23,200 --> 01:09:25,077
Hee-sun, you're pretty good.

1250
01:09:25,161 --> 01:09:27,830
- I think you're better than me.
- It's okay. It's better than one.

1251
01:09:27,913 --> 01:09:30,916
Honestly, I think it's only
because I drank this whole thing.

1252
01:09:31,000 --> 01:09:33,169
- I'm slightly tipsy right now.
- Oh, really?

1253
01:09:33,252 --> 01:09:35,588
Do you have to hold it
with all three fingers?

1254
01:09:36,297 --> 01:09:39,717
Okay, so you just shimmy, shimmy, shimmy,
and then whoosh!

1255
01:09:39,800 --> 01:09:41,051
Shimmy, shimmy, shimmy, whoosh!

1256
01:09:41,135 --> 01:09:43,470
You whooshed it
right into the gutter before.

1257
01:09:43,554 --> 01:09:46,056
Looked fine to me.

1258
01:09:49,185 --> 01:09:52,730
In a straight line.

1259
01:09:53,314 --> 01:09:55,065
What are you doing? Is this intentional?

1260
01:09:55,149 --> 01:09:56,483
- No.
- It's not cool.

1261
01:10:01,071 --> 01:10:02,239
Why does he have to be good?

1262
01:10:03,699 --> 01:10:06,410
- You've got the hang of it.
- Yeah.

1263
01:10:06,493 --> 01:10:08,078
Try to get a smooth release.

1264
01:10:11,498 --> 01:10:14,793
What the--

1265
01:10:16,212 --> 01:10:18,881
- What's going on here?
- What the--

1266
01:10:20,174 --> 01:10:23,010
- I step up when it counts.
- Amazing.

1267
01:10:23,093 --> 01:10:26,263
- There's nothing to it.
- What? I can't believe you.

1268
01:10:26,347 --> 01:10:29,850
- Oh, that's so annoying.
- Well, I do want to win actually.

1269
01:10:29,934 --> 01:10:32,686
- I really want to win, too.
- All right, Mina, let's go.

1270
01:10:33,562 --> 01:10:35,397
- Show them. Come on.
- I'll show you!

1271
01:10:35,481 --> 01:10:36,649
Show them what you got.

1272
01:10:41,362 --> 01:10:43,364
You always do better on your second try.

1273
01:10:43,447 --> 01:10:46,867
You'll get a strike if you bowl
from there, from the other side.

1274
01:10:49,328 --> 01:10:51,413
- Stop laughing.
- Give it a go.

1275
01:10:54,208 --> 01:10:56,752
Relax, relax.

1276
01:10:58,504 --> 01:11:00,422
Oh, you got it, you got it.

1277
01:11:01,131 --> 01:11:02,091
Oh!

1278
01:11:02,174 --> 01:11:03,759
Whoa!

1279
01:11:04,343 --> 01:11:05,344
I can't believe it.

1280
01:11:05,928 --> 01:11:07,054
I can't believe it.

1281
01:11:07,972 --> 01:11:10,099
Well, we're not gonna lose,
that's for sure.

1282
01:11:10,182 --> 01:11:12,351
- Oh, it's a spare.
- You're back in the game.

1283
01:11:12,434 --> 01:11:14,812
That was good. Thank goodness.

1284
01:11:17,523 --> 01:11:18,816
You sure these are okay?

1285
01:11:19,817 --> 01:11:23,404
- They definitely won't break?
- I hope not. My wrist hurts, actually.

1286
01:11:25,364 --> 01:11:26,365
What's wrong?

1287
01:11:26,448 --> 01:11:27,950
She looks irritated.

1288
01:11:28,033 --> 01:11:31,203
She really should be focusing
on her date with Seung-il, but…

1289
01:11:31,287 --> 01:11:32,329
But she can't.

1290
01:11:34,123 --> 01:11:35,749
Why are you looking upset?

1291
01:11:40,170 --> 01:11:44,258
Really, I'm fine. I'm just so bad at it.
I hate being the only one who sucks here.

1292
01:11:45,509 --> 01:11:47,928
My score is not even
that different from yours.

1293
01:11:48,470 --> 01:11:50,889
- Don't be so hard on us, okay?
- Okay.

1294
01:11:52,141 --> 01:11:55,352
- I really want to bowl a strike, too.
- At least once.

1295
01:11:56,061 --> 01:11:58,272
I'd be happy with just one strike.

1296
01:11:58,355 --> 01:12:00,941
Hey, guys, the professionals,
what am I doing wrong?

1297
01:12:01,025 --> 01:12:02,359
Could you please tell me?

1298
01:12:02,443 --> 01:12:04,778
Okay. I think you need to fix your legs.

1299
01:12:04,862 --> 01:12:07,823
- Legs? What about them?
- Yeah. You're moving them too fast.

1300
01:12:07,906 --> 01:12:09,992
- Slowly?
- Yeah.

1301
01:12:10,075 --> 01:12:12,119
She's had some coaching now.

1302
01:12:15,914 --> 01:12:16,999
That was good.

1303
01:12:17,583 --> 01:12:19,418
Oh, oh, oh!

1304
01:12:20,210 --> 01:12:21,754
Oh, oh, oh!

1305
01:12:22,921 --> 01:12:24,506
Whoa!

1306
01:12:26,508 --> 01:12:28,886
It's like she's possessed or something.

1307
01:12:28,969 --> 01:12:30,888
- Seriously.
- Su-been just had to speak.

1308
01:12:30,971 --> 01:12:32,014
Wow.

1309
01:12:32,848 --> 01:12:33,891
Ah. Oh!

1310
01:12:33,974 --> 01:12:36,185
I can't believe it!

1311
01:12:37,895 --> 01:12:39,146
This actually worked.

1312
01:12:39,229 --> 01:12:42,066
- That was it! That's the secret.
- Straight through. Just like this.

1313
01:12:42,149 --> 01:12:44,526
That was really nice. Hee-sun, you're up.

1314
01:12:45,486 --> 01:12:46,779
Crazy improvement.

1315
01:12:48,030 --> 01:12:49,740
You know me, I'm all about growth.

1316
01:12:59,500 --> 01:13:03,170
She reacts to everything Su-been says,
even if it's just something small.

1317
01:13:03,253 --> 01:13:06,006
What's even funnier is how Seung-il
was acting all confident,

1318
01:13:06,090 --> 01:13:07,966
saying something like,
"Don't worry, <i>noona,</i>

1319
01:13:08,050 --> 01:13:09,802
I'll make sure you forget all about him."

1320
01:13:09,885 --> 01:13:11,387
He's achieving absolutely nothing.

1321
01:13:11,470 --> 01:13:13,305
- His shoulders are so slumped.
- Yeah.

1322
01:13:15,557 --> 01:13:17,518
Oh, great. It's pizza.

1323
01:13:17,601 --> 01:13:19,269
Looks so good.

1324
01:13:19,353 --> 01:13:21,146
- Really great.
- It smells amazing.

1325
01:13:21,230 --> 01:13:23,148
- It looks good.
- Bon appétit.

1326
01:13:23,232 --> 01:13:24,858
Enjoy, everyone.

1327
01:13:24,942 --> 01:13:27,361
- Any toppings you don't like?
- I like it all.

1328
01:13:27,444 --> 01:13:29,780
- Pepperoni? Pepperoni?
- Yeah, sure.

1329
01:13:29,863 --> 01:13:32,116
- Pepperoni?
- What shall I eat?

1330
01:13:32,199 --> 01:13:33,492
So sweet. Thank you.

1331
01:13:34,243 --> 01:13:35,619
- I'll just have a bite.
- Thank you.

1332
01:13:35,702 --> 01:13:37,287
I'll just eat it like this.

1333
01:13:38,956 --> 01:13:40,040
Mmm…

1334
01:13:40,791 --> 01:13:43,585
- You drank a lot.
- Well, I was thirsty.

1335
01:13:52,886 --> 01:13:54,304
I'm curious about something.

1336
01:13:54,388 --> 01:13:56,306
- Can I ask you a question?
- Sure.

1337
01:13:56,390 --> 01:13:58,058
- What?
- I'm assuming you felt something,

1338
01:13:58,142 --> 01:14:01,145
some attraction at first,
to want to get to know each other, right?

1339
01:14:01,228 --> 01:14:04,064
So, what was it exactly
that attracted you to each other?

1340
01:14:04,148 --> 01:14:05,357
Mmm…

1341
01:14:09,862 --> 01:14:13,115
I've actually always said
he made the best first impression on me.

1342
01:14:13,198 --> 01:14:15,033
He makes a great first impression.

1343
01:14:15,117 --> 01:14:16,410
- Really?
- Yeah.

1344
01:14:16,493 --> 01:14:18,454
- I didn't know.
- The other thing was,

1345
01:14:19,288 --> 01:14:23,208
he and I paired up and did that
photo shoot challenge together.

1346
01:14:23,792 --> 01:14:26,003
And I think
that's when I started liking him.

1347
01:14:26,086 --> 01:14:28,589
I think there was something
about that photo shoot.

1348
01:14:29,214 --> 01:14:30,382
Similar for me as well.

1349
01:14:30,466 --> 01:14:33,844
We just happened
to get paired up for games,

1350
01:14:33,927 --> 01:14:37,848
and we ended up talking a lot
and eating together, too.

1351
01:14:37,931 --> 01:14:40,642
So I got intrigued about her. Mmm.

1352
01:14:40,726 --> 01:14:43,979
And as we kept talking,
I realized I felt comfortable with her.

1353
01:14:44,062 --> 01:14:47,441
The more I get to know her,
the more I'm seeing sides to her I like.

1354
01:14:47,524 --> 01:14:48,525
Mmm.

1355
01:14:49,026 --> 01:14:53,280
Yeah, so that's what made me
want to come to Paradise with her.

1356
01:14:54,072 --> 01:14:55,407
They're adorable together.

1357
01:14:55,491 --> 01:14:57,659
- You guys are really cute.
- Yeah.

1358
01:15:03,582 --> 01:15:05,709
I've been curious
to hear from you as well.

1359
01:15:05,792 --> 01:15:07,169
Curious about what?

1360
01:15:07,878 --> 01:15:09,922
You've been interested in her
from the start, right?

1361
01:15:10,506 --> 01:15:13,926
- My feelings haven't changed.
- You were curious about her right away.

1362
01:15:14,885 --> 01:15:18,055
I've always been drawn to girls
who have a more mature vibe.

1363
01:15:18,138 --> 01:15:19,389
I find that attractive.

1364
01:15:19,473 --> 01:15:22,518
Since I got here,
we've had meaningful conversations,

1365
01:15:22,601 --> 01:15:25,521
even about the smallest,
most trivial things.

1366
01:15:25,604 --> 01:15:27,272
Not just surface-level stuff.

1367
01:15:27,356 --> 01:15:30,359
We make an effort to open up
and learn more about each other.

1368
01:15:31,527 --> 01:15:35,405
Yeah, we've also talked a lot today,
like over dinner earlier.

1369
01:15:36,114 --> 01:15:38,534
And we feel like we have more in common
than we thought.

1370
01:15:38,617 --> 01:15:40,494
- Mmm.
- Like one of us says something,

1371
01:15:40,577 --> 01:15:43,664
- and the other is like… Uh-huh.
- "Oh, oh." That?

1372
01:15:43,747 --> 01:15:45,374
"You, too?"

1373
01:15:45,457 --> 01:15:47,459
- It wasn't like we were trying.
- Exactly.

1374
01:15:47,543 --> 01:15:50,087
Stuff like that kept happening
randomly on its own.

1375
01:15:50,170 --> 01:15:51,880
Kind of weird, honestly, but cool.

1376
01:15:53,382 --> 01:15:55,300
- I see.
- I see.

1377
01:15:59,888 --> 01:16:01,265
This is yummy.

1378
01:16:02,933 --> 01:16:04,434
- Oh, it's good?
- Mmm-hmm.

1379
01:16:05,686 --> 01:16:07,354
I'm full, but I can't stop.

1380
01:16:09,189 --> 01:16:11,900
Let's eat more when we get back.
Stop eating.

1381
01:16:15,654 --> 01:16:18,699
So how did you and Min-gee
get so close so quickly, then?

1382
01:16:19,283 --> 01:16:20,742
- Mmm.
- Hold on.

1383
01:16:20,826 --> 01:16:25,205
Why isn't anyone asking me how I decided
to come to Paradise with Seung-il?

1384
01:16:25,289 --> 01:16:26,290
I know, right?

1385
01:16:26,373 --> 01:16:28,792
- Are they not interested?
- Can't you ask me?

1386
01:16:28,875 --> 01:16:31,878
- I won't tell if you don't want to know.
- Sorry. How did you decide?

1387
01:16:32,421 --> 01:16:35,465
- Hee-sun, you're funny.
- Aren't you a T?

1388
01:16:35,549 --> 01:16:37,092
Well, I couldn't ask you.

1389
01:16:37,175 --> 01:16:38,719
- Why?
- Well…

1390
01:16:39,261 --> 01:16:42,931
Mina, I really want to know.
Seriously, I do.

1391
01:16:43,015 --> 01:16:45,434
Do you remember earlier on in Inferno,

1392
01:16:46,018 --> 01:16:49,688
we had to show who we were interested in
with those postcards, right?

1393
01:16:49,771 --> 01:16:51,023
Oh, I see.

1394
01:16:51,106 --> 01:16:53,400
- I gave mine to Seung-il.
- I knew she did.

1395
01:16:53,483 --> 01:16:57,321
- You did?
- I kind of made it obvious.

1396
01:16:57,404 --> 01:17:00,240
But then the next day,
I thought I didn't have a chance

1397
01:17:00,324 --> 01:17:02,701
because he was already with someone else.

1398
01:17:02,784 --> 01:17:06,496
So I ended up going to Paradise with a guy
who I put as my second choice.

1399
01:17:06,580 --> 01:17:10,250
Then, at the campfire, I found out like,
"Oh, he actually is into me."

1400
01:17:10,334 --> 01:17:12,210
- The chocolate.
- Right, the chocolate.

1401
01:17:13,086 --> 01:17:16,673
The chocolate made me realize
that I wasn't delusional and making it up.

1402
01:17:17,257 --> 01:17:19,551
I felt I needed time to get to know him.

1403
01:17:19,635 --> 01:17:23,889
- So, that's what happened.
- Wow.

1404
01:17:26,975 --> 01:17:29,686
- You made the right choice.
- It's worked out.

1405
01:17:30,729 --> 01:17:33,357
- You too.
- Get to know each other better.

1406
01:17:36,151 --> 01:17:39,196
Yeah, I mean, since this is
my second time in Paradise,

1407
01:17:39,279 --> 01:17:41,031
I came in with a whole new mindset,

1408
01:17:41,114 --> 01:17:45,118
thinking of all those things I didn't get
to experience the first time around.

1409
01:17:45,202 --> 01:17:47,996
There were things I wanted to do
but didn't manage to

1410
01:17:48,080 --> 01:17:50,082
- since it was my first time.
- Mmm.

1411
01:17:50,165 --> 01:17:51,625
I'm finding myself

1412
01:17:51,708 --> 01:17:54,503
stepping out of my comfort zone more
on the second trip.

1413
01:17:54,586 --> 01:17:58,715
I mean, look, of course, that first trip
was special in its own way.

1414
01:17:58,799 --> 01:18:02,761
But, today, I experienced fun things,
you know, like driving and stuff.

1415
01:18:02,844 --> 01:18:06,264
- That's been really nice this time around.
- Mmm.

1416
01:18:07,474 --> 01:18:09,851
- Yeah.
- Bet that felt good.

1417
01:18:13,397 --> 01:18:15,357
What did I just watch?

1418
01:18:15,440 --> 01:18:18,735
- "You too." "Bet that felt good."
- Yeah.

1419
01:18:18,819 --> 01:18:21,446
She finally got to do
what she's been wanting to.

1420
01:18:21,530 --> 01:18:25,242
There's literally an invisible duel
going on right in front of our eyes.

1421
01:18:25,325 --> 01:18:27,327
- You know, those two.
- Ah.

1422
01:18:29,496 --> 01:18:31,707
- Yeah.
- Bet that felt good.

1423
01:18:31,790 --> 01:18:33,709
What do you mean?

1424
01:18:33,792 --> 01:18:36,920
I just mean you're doing things
you didn't get to before,

1425
01:18:37,003 --> 01:18:39,256
so you won't have any regrets or anything.

1426
01:18:39,965 --> 01:18:42,259
- You won't get this opportunity again.
- Mmm.

1427
01:18:42,342 --> 01:18:43,927
Well, you never know.

1428
01:18:55,355 --> 01:18:56,440
So funny.

1429
01:18:58,650 --> 01:19:01,445
- I'm gonna sleep so well.
- Same, like a baby.

1430
01:19:03,113 --> 01:19:04,948
What are you gonna do at the hotel?

1431
01:19:05,490 --> 01:19:06,742
Maybe the pool?

1432
01:19:08,160 --> 01:19:10,328
Yeah. Why not? Even just for a little.

1433
01:19:10,412 --> 01:19:13,123
Or we could just sleep in the pool.

1434
01:19:13,206 --> 01:19:16,918
- In the pool?
- Your skin will go wrinkly.

1435
01:19:20,881 --> 01:19:22,257
From the couples' point of view,

1436
01:19:22,340 --> 01:19:24,634
this was probably
the most awkward combination

1437
01:19:24,718 --> 01:19:26,386
you could've imagined for a double date.

1438
01:19:26,470 --> 01:19:29,264
Mina Sue kept pushing Su-been's buttons
in front of Hee-sun,

1439
01:19:29,347 --> 01:19:31,725
so there was this constant tension
that you couldn't ignore.

1440
01:19:31,808 --> 01:19:33,560
For sure. After holding back,

1441
01:19:33,643 --> 01:19:36,104
this is how he ended up
responding to her provoking him.

1442
01:19:36,188 --> 01:19:38,899
It was starting to look like
another lovers' quarrel.

1443
01:19:38,982 --> 01:19:41,234
- Yeah.
- Will the cycle keep repeating itself?

1444
01:19:41,318 --> 01:19:44,905
Mina Sue says, "I'm sorry,"
and they make up, and it keeps on going.

1445
01:19:44,988 --> 01:19:46,239
- Right.
- Mmm.

1446
01:19:46,323 --> 01:19:49,659
I thought he had actually developed
feelings for Hee-sun.

1447
01:19:49,743 --> 01:19:53,246
It seemed set in stone.
But, immediately, things went wrong again.

1448
01:19:53,830 --> 01:19:56,208
So the whole situation
feels uncertain to me.

1449
01:19:56,291 --> 01:19:59,044
I can't imagine how Hee-sun
and Seung-il must be feeling.

1450
01:19:59,127 --> 01:20:02,422
Hee-sun looks like
she's at a complete loss. Mmm.

1451
01:20:05,258 --> 01:20:08,553
Wow, this place is huge.

1452
01:20:10,013 --> 01:20:11,640
- It's so pretty.
- Let's go in.

1453
01:20:13,141 --> 01:20:16,436
- Flowers look different from last time.
- Mmm.

1454
01:20:17,854 --> 01:20:19,105
They're real flowers.

1455
01:20:19,189 --> 01:20:20,524
- Are they really?
- Yeah.

1456
01:20:24,277 --> 01:20:25,779
Wow.

1457
01:20:26,738 --> 01:20:28,156
It's so nice.

1458
01:20:28,240 --> 01:20:29,616
The water's warm.

1459
01:20:29,699 --> 01:20:30,992
- Really?
- This one's really warm.

1460
01:20:31,076 --> 01:20:34,454
- I want to try that one.
- Once you're in, you don't want to leave.

1461
01:20:34,538 --> 01:20:36,081
- Looks amazing.
- Yeah.

1462
01:20:36,665 --> 01:20:38,583
- I'm gonna have to get in here.
- Yeah.

1463
01:20:39,167 --> 01:20:40,335
Nice, nice, nice.

1464
01:20:40,418 --> 01:20:42,629
- Should we order something and hang out?
- Should we eat?

1465
01:20:42,712 --> 01:20:44,381
- Yeah. You want to?
- Yeah.

1466
01:20:44,464 --> 01:20:45,465
Sounds good.

1467
01:20:45,549 --> 01:20:48,051
We can see them in their pool from here.

1468
01:20:48,134 --> 01:20:49,886
- Whose room is that?
- Hyun-jae's.

1469
01:20:49,970 --> 01:20:52,430
Oh, really?
I thought it might have been Su-been's.

1470
01:20:59,145 --> 01:21:00,564
So annoying.

1471
01:21:18,248 --> 01:21:20,542
- She really is so forward.
- Jeez.

1472
01:21:20,625 --> 01:21:22,168
She's trying to find his room?

1473
01:21:22,252 --> 01:21:24,921
Wait. Is she looking
for Su-been in the pool?

1474
01:21:25,005 --> 01:21:26,590
- Yeah, she is.
- Seriously?

1475
01:21:28,967 --> 01:21:31,303
Her head is just
full of thoughts of Su-been.

1476
01:21:43,440 --> 01:21:44,774
So annoying.

1477
01:21:49,446 --> 01:21:51,531
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1478
01:22:01,708 --> 01:22:03,835
I haven't swam in a long time.

1479
01:22:16,097 --> 01:22:19,517
- You're really good. Wow.
- Told you I'm a good swimmer.

1480
01:22:24,481 --> 01:22:26,483
- I'm good, right?
- Yeah, you are.

1481
01:22:26,566 --> 01:22:28,068
Whoa!

1482
01:22:28,151 --> 01:22:30,737
Now, no touching the bottom.

1483
01:22:35,241 --> 01:22:36,910
- You're a slow poke.
- I held back.

1484
01:22:39,287 --> 01:22:40,622
You're still good, though.

1485
01:22:42,666 --> 01:22:44,793
A big change
from Inferno's freezing water.

1486
01:22:57,430 --> 01:22:59,933
I feel like I've changed a lot today.

1487
01:23:01,393 --> 01:23:03,436
- Your feelings?
- Yeah.

1488
01:23:06,564 --> 01:23:08,149
How have they changed?

1489
01:23:12,696 --> 01:23:14,197
They've solidified.

1490
01:23:21,496 --> 01:23:23,915
I tend to get fixated on a single thing.

1491
01:23:23,999 --> 01:23:25,834
- Mmm.
- Yeah.

1492
01:23:25,917 --> 01:23:28,336
- We're so similar.
- Oh, really?

1493
01:23:29,504 --> 01:23:30,922
I'm not good at juggling things.

1494
01:23:31,006 --> 01:23:34,050
Once I fixate on something,
I can't focus on anything else.

1495
01:23:34,134 --> 01:23:35,552
- Oh, really?
- Mmm.

1496
01:23:37,554 --> 01:23:38,555
I'm the same.

1497
01:23:50,483 --> 01:23:51,484
Oh.

1498
01:23:52,527 --> 01:23:53,778
This looks good.

1499
01:23:55,321 --> 01:23:57,699
- She's still looking?
- Really?

1500
01:23:57,782 --> 01:24:01,494
- Unbelievable.
- My goodness. She's going way too far now.

1501
01:24:01,578 --> 01:24:05,373
- What, with Seung-il sitting right there?
- He saw her. Seung-il saw her.

1502
01:24:05,457 --> 01:24:06,666
No, he hasn't.

1503
01:24:06,750 --> 01:24:09,252
There's no way
he'll know she's looking for him.

1504
01:24:09,335 --> 01:24:11,504
He'll just assume
she's looking at the view.

1505
01:24:13,506 --> 01:24:14,674
This looks good.

1506
01:24:23,933 --> 01:24:26,519
- I mean, we don't have to overeat.
- Yeah, good idea.

1507
01:24:26,603 --> 01:24:27,604
Oh.

1508
01:24:30,815 --> 01:24:32,150
How are you feeling?

1509
01:24:32,734 --> 01:24:34,778
- Well, I am--
- You must be tired.

1510
01:24:34,861 --> 01:24:36,863
I'm a bit tired, but I'm okay.

1511
01:24:39,282 --> 01:24:41,743
It's just that I might not get
another chance to come back.

1512
01:24:41,826 --> 01:24:43,286
- To Paradise?
- Mmm.

1513
01:24:45,205 --> 01:24:48,917
- This is our last supper.
- Yeah. Cheers.

1514
01:24:52,003 --> 01:24:53,004
Mmm.

1515
01:24:58,176 --> 01:24:59,177
Mmm.

1516
01:25:01,346 --> 01:25:04,057
- Aren't you tired?
- Me? Not at all.

1517
01:25:06,184 --> 01:25:10,230
I had lots of fun. Mmm.
I was tired, but yeah.

1518
01:25:10,772 --> 01:25:14,484
- You? You did seem really tired.
- I was tired. Yeah.

1519
01:25:14,567 --> 01:25:16,444
- Wasn't that annoying for you?
- Why?

1520
01:25:18,488 --> 01:25:20,865
- Because you were tired?
- Nothing. Never mind.

1521
01:25:23,034 --> 01:25:25,787
Tell me, do I still seem
like someone born in '01?

1522
01:25:31,167 --> 01:25:34,712
It didn't even occur to me
that I'd be older than you.

1523
01:25:34,796 --> 01:25:38,424
Not at all? I'm kind of naive, though.
Doesn't that make me seem younger?

1524
01:25:38,508 --> 01:25:40,051
You don't seem younger.

1525
01:25:41,010 --> 01:25:43,096
What do you think a younger guy is like?

1526
01:25:43,179 --> 01:25:45,348
- Like Su-been. Su-been.
- Huh?

1527
01:25:45,431 --> 01:25:47,600
I realized I like cute guys.

1528
01:25:48,184 --> 01:25:50,270
- I'm sure now.
- "Cute guys"?

1529
01:25:51,813 --> 01:25:53,064
What's a cute guy?

1530
01:25:54,732 --> 01:25:57,110
- Mmm.
- So did Su-been call you "<i>noona"?</i>

1531
01:26:00,738 --> 01:26:02,157
Yeah, he did.

1532
01:26:02,240 --> 01:26:05,410
Actually, I was almost swayed yesterday.

1533
01:26:05,493 --> 01:26:07,662
No, not almost, I was swayed quite a lot

1534
01:26:07,745 --> 01:26:09,622
- because when we were--
- When you were talking.

1535
01:26:09,706 --> 01:26:11,624
Me and Su-been had a one-on-one chat.

1536
01:26:12,167 --> 01:26:15,712
And I told Su-been to call me "<i>noona"</i>
when we're alone.

1537
01:26:15,795 --> 01:26:20,133
He went, <i>"Noona," </i>and I thought I was
going to have a nosebleed.

1538
01:26:21,634 --> 01:26:23,344
Never mind.

1539
01:26:25,096 --> 01:26:26,097
<i>Noona.</i>

1540
01:26:26,848 --> 01:26:27,807
Like that?

1541
01:26:27,891 --> 01:26:30,018
Ugh, don't. I'm not feeling it.

1542
01:26:39,944 --> 01:26:43,740
Don't you think that your first
Paradise trip feels like your first love?

1543
01:26:43,823 --> 01:26:48,077
Like, everything's so intense
and fun and exciting.

1544
01:26:48,786 --> 01:26:50,580
- No, not for me.
- Really?

1545
01:26:50,663 --> 01:26:52,916
- More about who you went with.
- Party pooper.

1546
01:26:52,999 --> 01:26:55,251
So, for example, I was here with Su-been.

1547
01:26:55,335 --> 01:26:57,754
It wasn't like
I was really into him or anything.

1548
01:26:57,837 --> 01:27:00,298
- It was just…
- But it's really stuck with you?

1549
01:27:00,381 --> 01:27:01,591
Yeah.

1550
01:27:01,674 --> 01:27:05,762
I'm so sorry, I feel like I'm just talking
about someone else the entire time.

1551
01:27:05,845 --> 01:27:07,764
No, it's okay. I like listening, too.

1552
01:27:08,348 --> 01:27:10,016
Okay, I have a question.

1553
01:27:10,099 --> 01:27:12,560
Ask anything. I'll be honest with you.

1554
01:27:12,644 --> 01:27:14,896
- If you were to win a girls' game…
- Mmm.

1555
01:27:16,064 --> 01:27:17,815
…who'd you come to Paradise with?

1556
01:27:17,899 --> 01:27:19,901
- I'd choose Sung-hun.
- Sung-hun?

1557
01:27:21,903 --> 01:27:24,155
- Wow. Seriously?
- Wow.

1558
01:27:26,783 --> 01:27:29,369
I mean, wouldn't you have thought
she'd say Su-been?

1559
01:27:30,245 --> 01:27:32,956
I'm so confused. Completely thrown off.

1560
01:27:33,039 --> 01:27:34,540
I just got whiplash.

1561
01:27:36,334 --> 01:27:38,544
- If you were to win a girls' game…
- Mmm.

1562
01:27:39,629 --> 01:27:41,381
…who'd you come to Paradise with?

1563
01:27:41,464 --> 01:27:43,299
- I'd choose Sung-hun.
- Sung-hun?

1564
01:27:43,383 --> 01:27:45,134
You want to learn more about him?

1565
01:27:45,218 --> 01:27:48,972
It's more so that it could be the last
Paradise trip if you think about it.

1566
01:27:49,055 --> 01:27:51,766
So I really want Sung-hun
to experience this place.

1567
01:27:51,849 --> 01:27:55,019
And I also think it would be nice for him
to come here with me.

1568
01:27:57,814 --> 01:28:00,692
Mmm. What a fascinating person.

1569
01:28:00,775 --> 01:28:02,110
- I am?
- Yeah.

1570
01:28:02,193 --> 01:28:04,362
- My mind wouldn't have worked that way.
- Oh, really?

1571
01:28:06,322 --> 01:28:08,741
So there's someone
you're curious about. Okay.

1572
01:28:08,825 --> 01:28:11,494
What I don't get is,
do you want to take Sung-hun

1573
01:28:11,577 --> 01:28:14,497
- because you're actually into him or…
- I am.

1574
01:28:14,580 --> 01:28:17,959
Is that it? I think you need to figure out
what your real motive is.

1575
01:28:18,042 --> 01:28:20,670
If you're just doing it
out of consideration for him,

1576
01:28:20,753 --> 01:28:23,089
I think you're actually
doing him a disservice.

1577
01:28:25,049 --> 01:28:27,176
- You think? But Sung-hun…
- Yeah.

1578
01:28:28,011 --> 01:28:29,304
- You think so?
- Yeah.

1579
01:28:29,387 --> 01:28:31,514
So let's say you come with Sung-hun.

1580
01:28:31,597 --> 01:28:32,598
Mmm.

1581
01:28:33,308 --> 01:28:35,435
How would that make you feel?

1582
01:28:36,185 --> 01:28:39,147
What feelings are you going to base
your final choice on?

1583
01:28:41,899 --> 01:28:44,736
If I'm coming to Paradise with someone,
it's to get to know them.

1584
01:28:44,819 --> 01:28:47,530
It should be someone that I'm considering
for my final choice.

1585
01:28:47,613 --> 01:28:48,698
Mmm.

1586
01:28:48,781 --> 01:28:50,742
See, I don't know what my feelings are.

1587
01:28:50,825 --> 01:28:53,661
I'm confused. That's why…
I don't know, but…

1588
01:28:55,663 --> 01:28:57,415
I don't know, but I care about him.

1589
01:28:57,498 --> 01:29:01,586
Like earlier today, before we did
the Paradise-bound couples' matching--

1590
01:29:01,669 --> 01:29:03,129
- You talked?
- Yeah.

1591
01:29:03,212 --> 01:29:04,714
I said, "See you later."

1592
01:29:04,797 --> 01:29:07,133
"Are your feelings still the same,
by the way?"

1593
01:29:07,216 --> 01:29:09,844
He said yes,
so how can I not get to know him?

1594
01:29:09,927 --> 01:29:13,264
He says he has feelings for me,
and he's not interested in anyone else.

1595
01:29:13,848 --> 01:29:15,767
Well, what I want to know is,

1596
01:29:15,850 --> 01:29:18,936
why get to know him
just because he's not into anyone else?

1597
01:29:19,020 --> 01:29:22,315
I'm busy focusing on my own feelings
and the person I like.

1598
01:29:22,398 --> 01:29:25,109
I don't have the capacity
to take care of him, too.

1599
01:29:25,193 --> 01:29:26,944
That's what I'd be thinking.

1600
01:29:27,028 --> 01:29:30,239
You do have a point actually.
I'll keep that in mind.

1601
01:29:32,742 --> 01:29:34,535
- Up to you.
- I'll keep it in mind.

1602
01:29:34,619 --> 01:29:35,620
That's all I can do.

1603
01:29:36,412 --> 01:29:39,707
This is giving me lots to think about.

1604
01:29:45,046 --> 01:29:46,214
It's so hard.

1605
01:29:52,887 --> 01:29:55,223
My mind's suddenly in overdrive.

1606
01:29:58,351 --> 01:30:00,853
Isn't it pretty simple,
as far as you're concerned?

1607
01:30:00,937 --> 01:30:03,606
All you need to do
is have a talk with Sung-hun.

1608
01:30:03,689 --> 01:30:05,900
I really need to talk to Su-been, too.

1609
01:30:10,405 --> 01:30:13,408
- The vibe has died.
- Yeah, it totally has.

1610
01:30:15,827 --> 01:30:18,121
I really need to talk to Su-been, too.

1611
01:30:24,335 --> 01:30:26,838
Well, that's up to you.
I don't know anymore.

1612
01:30:26,921 --> 01:30:28,214
You do what you want.

1613
01:30:28,297 --> 01:30:31,217
No. Well, it's just that that I…

1614
01:30:31,300 --> 01:30:32,844
No.

1615
01:30:33,845 --> 01:30:36,222
For real, if I get another chance
to come to Paradise,

1616
01:30:36,305 --> 01:30:37,932
I'm going to come with Sung-hun.

1617
01:30:39,684 --> 01:30:41,853
- That's what I'll do.
- Whatever you want.

1618
01:30:41,936 --> 01:30:44,147
- I will do whatever I want.
- Sure.

1619
01:30:44,230 --> 01:30:45,940
- Don't tell me what to do.
- Me?

1620
01:30:46,524 --> 01:30:50,194
- Did I tell you what to do?
- I'll do what I want.

1621
01:30:51,737 --> 01:30:52,989
Mmm.

1622
01:30:58,202 --> 01:31:00,246
I wonder what'll happen. We'll find out.

1623
01:31:01,747 --> 01:31:04,208
I've really enjoyed the time
we spent in Paradise,

1624
01:31:04,292 --> 01:31:06,127
but I'm ready to go back to Inferno.

1625
01:31:06,878 --> 01:31:09,088
- I'm curious how things are over there.
- Mmm.

1626
01:31:09,172 --> 01:31:10,673
- I want to leave.
- Huh?

1627
01:31:10,756 --> 01:31:13,301
I'm over it in here. I'm stressed out.

1628
01:31:14,218 --> 01:31:17,472
- He's throwing in the towel.
- He's done.

1629
01:31:17,555 --> 01:31:19,807
He's washing his hands of this.
Yeah, yeah.

1630
01:31:19,891 --> 01:31:21,851
- Wow.
- Seung-il's given up.

1631
01:31:21,934 --> 01:31:24,520
- He's missing Min-gee.
- He can't wait to get back.

1632
01:31:24,604 --> 01:31:28,774
I have to admit, it feels really good
that Seung-il has voiced even a small part

1633
01:31:28,858 --> 01:31:32,820
of what I've been wanting to say to her
for pretty much the entire time.

1634
01:31:33,446 --> 01:31:37,700
Honestly speaking, there's a limit
to what we panelists can say.

1635
01:31:37,783 --> 01:31:39,952
So when a fellow contestant
speaks up like that,

1636
01:31:40,036 --> 01:31:42,246
it's so satisfying for viewers,
including us.

1637
01:31:42,330 --> 01:31:43,456
Yeah, for sure.

1638
01:31:43,539 --> 01:31:46,667
We actually get pulled in
by the production team during breaks

1639
01:31:46,751 --> 01:31:50,254
and get told things like,
"What you said was way too harsh."

1640
01:31:50,338 --> 01:31:53,799
And after the training session,
we come back and tone things down,

1641
01:31:53,883 --> 01:31:56,427
and we're careful
with how far we take things.

1642
01:31:56,511 --> 01:31:58,930
So Seung-il really took one
for the team today.

1643
01:31:59,013 --> 01:32:02,600
Seung-il totally lost it at the end there.
He couldn't do it anymore.

1644
01:32:03,142 --> 01:32:05,144
He's not the type to lose his temper,
but he did.

1645
01:32:05,228 --> 01:32:08,856
He kept on holding it in,
and then, "This is just not right."

1646
01:32:09,440 --> 01:32:10,566
It's too bad.

1647
01:32:17,532 --> 01:32:19,075
Are you gonna dry your hair?

1648
01:32:19,158 --> 01:32:21,327
- Do you need to dry your hair?
- Sorry? I do.

1649
01:32:22,036 --> 01:32:24,121
- Come dry it.
- I'm really quick.

1650
01:32:26,207 --> 01:32:29,544
- I'm really bad at styling my hair.
- How come?

1651
01:32:29,627 --> 01:32:31,546
Because my head is kind of wide.

1652
01:32:35,341 --> 01:32:37,468
- Ah, yeah.
- It's pretty wide, isn't it?

1653
01:32:37,552 --> 01:32:38,761
- This part?
- Exactly.

1654
01:32:40,763 --> 01:32:42,682
- Done already?
- This is how I always do it.

1655
01:32:44,141 --> 01:32:46,143
- Hair oil?
- Hair essence.

1656
01:32:49,772 --> 01:32:51,524
- It's nice.
- It is.

1657
01:32:58,406 --> 01:33:00,741
You look similar with and without makeup.

1658
01:33:01,742 --> 01:33:03,202
- Do I?
- Yeah.

1659
01:33:03,286 --> 01:33:07,915
Well, I mean, it's not exactly the same,

1660
01:33:07,999 --> 01:33:10,626
- but it's really close.
- I wear it to look different.

1661
01:33:10,710 --> 01:33:13,588
- Face masks?
- Yeah. I'll get you one?

1662
01:33:13,671 --> 01:33:14,672
Sure.

1663
01:33:15,214 --> 01:33:17,049
They look comfortable together.

1664
01:33:17,133 --> 01:33:19,218
It's what young love
in your twenties is like.

1665
01:33:21,137 --> 01:33:23,222
I'm really bad with stuff like this.

1666
01:33:23,306 --> 01:33:24,557
Oh.

1667
01:33:25,850 --> 01:33:27,518
Bear with me.

1668
01:33:28,019 --> 01:33:29,103
Okay, I got it.

1669
01:33:35,901 --> 01:33:38,237
Wait. Oh, this-- Hold on.

1670
01:33:40,448 --> 01:33:42,825
- Is this right?
- Yeah.

1671
01:33:43,576 --> 01:33:44,660
I'm not done yet.

1672
01:33:46,746 --> 01:33:49,582
Wow. Your forehead really does stick out.

1673
01:33:51,125 --> 01:33:55,087
No, wait. No, don't laugh.
No, don't laugh. Stop laughing.

1674
01:33:55,171 --> 01:33:57,632
I need to try and stick this on.

1675
01:33:59,675 --> 01:34:01,469
There. Open your eyes.

1676
01:34:02,762 --> 01:34:05,640
You did it wrong, didn't you?

1677
01:34:05,723 --> 01:34:08,851
- No, it's just a tiny bit crooked.
- It looks weird.

1678
01:34:09,352 --> 01:34:11,854
- Just a little.
- It's crooked here.

1679
01:34:11,937 --> 01:34:13,564
- Hold on.
- You need to center it.

1680
01:34:13,648 --> 01:34:14,649
Wait a minute.

1681
01:34:15,191 --> 01:34:17,526
- Oh, seriously.
- Stay still.

1682
01:34:19,487 --> 01:34:22,031
- They're standing close.
- Looks like they'll kiss.

1683
01:34:22,114 --> 01:34:23,366
Kiss, kiss!

1684
01:34:24,283 --> 01:34:27,703
Sir, excuse me. You're being improper.
What's the matter with you?

1685
01:34:27,787 --> 01:34:28,913
They did look ready to kiss.

1686
01:34:28,996 --> 01:34:30,831
Been too long
since I was young and innocent.

1687
01:34:34,960 --> 01:34:35,920
There.

1688
01:34:36,003 --> 01:34:37,254
- You sure?
- Yes.

1689
01:34:38,130 --> 01:34:40,049
- It's good, right?
- Oh, yeah. Good job.

1690
01:34:40,758 --> 01:34:42,551
Took you a while, but…

1691
01:34:45,554 --> 01:34:47,139
Come here. I'll do yours now.

1692
01:34:52,978 --> 01:34:55,398
- Feel good?
- Mmm. Yeah.

1693
01:34:55,481 --> 01:34:56,440
Pull it up a bit.

1694
01:34:57,733 --> 01:34:59,110
- Wait.
- Hey, why is--

1695
01:34:59,193 --> 01:35:00,986
- You're too tall.
- I look like No Face.

1696
01:35:01,070 --> 01:35:02,571
- Come on.
- You're too tall.

1697
01:35:02,655 --> 01:35:04,490
- It needs to be higher.
- Like this.

1698
01:35:04,573 --> 01:35:06,492
- Yeah.
- It's because my arms are tired.

1699
01:35:09,954 --> 01:35:10,913
Lie down.

1700
01:35:12,289 --> 01:35:14,667
If there's another chance
to come back to Paradise,

1701
01:35:14,750 --> 01:35:15,960
I'm going to go all out.

1702
01:35:16,544 --> 01:35:20,089
- Totally.
- Yeah. Whether it's a game or a challenge.

1703
01:35:20,881 --> 01:35:22,341
Who will you bring?

1704
01:35:24,093 --> 01:35:25,177
Wanna know?

1705
01:35:26,220 --> 01:35:27,221
No.

1706
01:35:28,764 --> 01:35:30,349
Why not?

1707
01:35:30,433 --> 01:35:31,434
Why not?

1708
01:35:31,934 --> 01:35:33,269
I'm scared.

1709
01:35:37,022 --> 01:35:40,860
Your pose right now is very seductive.

1710
01:35:41,610 --> 01:35:42,820
I don't want to go back.

1711
01:35:43,738 --> 01:35:45,531
- To Inferno?
- Mmm-hmm.

1712
01:35:45,614 --> 01:35:49,744
Just make sure you get to come back here,
or turn Inferno into Paradise.

1713
01:35:49,827 --> 01:35:50,953
Yeah.

1714
01:35:53,164 --> 01:35:55,541
- Let's sleep.
- Good night.

1715
01:35:56,500 --> 01:35:58,002
Isn't it a bit cold?

1716
01:35:58,085 --> 01:36:01,046
Oh, I'm going to sleep with the hoodie on.

1717
01:36:01,130 --> 01:36:02,173
Yeah.

1718
01:36:02,256 --> 01:36:04,675
- I always have it on.
- You can keep it.

1719
01:36:05,342 --> 01:36:08,512
- It's basically mine now.
- It is.

1720
01:36:09,597 --> 01:36:11,640
- Her security blanket.
- It's become her safety net.

1721
01:36:11,724 --> 01:36:12,725
Yeah.

1722
01:36:13,768 --> 01:36:16,187
Seriously, that hoodie,
it's making me laugh.

1723
01:36:16,270 --> 01:36:19,398
I think Su-been's heart
will be pretty set on Hee-sun

1724
01:36:19,482 --> 01:36:21,442
after this trip to Paradise.

1725
01:36:21,525 --> 01:36:22,526
But…

1726
01:36:23,319 --> 01:36:26,489
- Don't say "but."
- Oh, just be quiet, will you, please?

1727
01:36:26,572 --> 01:36:28,699
You always have to argue about everything.

1728
01:36:28,783 --> 01:36:31,535
But Mina Sue does not
take things lying down.

1729
01:36:31,619 --> 01:36:34,288
- Everything will change.
- She'll get between them.

1730
01:36:34,371 --> 01:36:37,291
Is a dark shadow creeping up
on those two once again?

1731
01:36:37,374 --> 01:36:41,170
My cards are all crumpled up
because this is so anxiety-inducing.

1732
01:36:41,253 --> 01:36:43,923
While watching Mina Sue,
I needed emotional support.

1733
01:36:44,006 --> 01:36:46,425
I grabbed the cards
and folded them into a plate.

1734
01:36:46,509 --> 01:36:49,512
Maybe if the cards feel more stable,
my emotions will follow.

1735
01:36:49,595 --> 01:36:52,264
This season is so crazy.

1736
01:36:58,938 --> 01:37:00,773
- Filming…
- Did you swim?

1737
01:37:00,856 --> 01:37:01,816
Yeah.

1738
01:37:01,899 --> 01:37:04,568
Su-been, were you wearing white
in the pool yesterday?

1739
01:37:05,319 --> 01:37:08,113
- White and green. Why?
- Oh, okay, it was you.

1740
01:37:08,197 --> 01:37:09,824
- Yeah?
- Did you see us?

1741
01:37:09,907 --> 01:37:11,325
We could see you from above.

1742
01:37:11,408 --> 01:37:12,868
- You saw?
- Mmm.

1743
01:37:12,952 --> 01:37:15,162
- No way.
- What floor were you on?

1744
01:37:15,246 --> 01:37:16,789
- The 12th.
- Mmm.

1745
01:37:16,872 --> 01:37:17,873
- Yeah.
- Oh.

1746
01:37:17,957 --> 01:37:21,001
- Were you in the same room as last time?
- Yeah, the exact same room.

1747
01:37:30,511 --> 01:37:33,097
I feel like I'm gonna throw up.
I might be sick.

1748
01:37:33,722 --> 01:37:35,224
- I feel like…
- Motion sickness?

1749
01:37:45,192 --> 01:37:46,277
- Mina Sue.
- Will she notice?

1750
01:37:46,360 --> 01:37:47,236
For sure.
